    <h2>Understanding Child Labour</h2>

    <div class="card">
        <h3>Why Child Labour Occurs</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Poverty and unemployment</li>
            <li>Lack of access to quality schooling</li>
            <li>Weak law enforcement</li>
            <li>Demand for cheap labour</li>
            <li>Trafficking and exploitation</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
        <h3>Child Protection Laws in India</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Child Labour (Prohibition & Regulation) Act, 1986</strong></li>
            <li><strong>Right to Education Act (RTE)</strong> - free education for children 6-14</li>
            <li><strong>Juvenile Justice Act, 2015</strong> - strict penalties for exploitation</li>
            <li><strong>POSCO Act</strong> - protection from sexual offences</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
        <h3>How Communities Can Help</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Report suspicious child labour cases</li>
            <li>Encourage families to enroll children in school</li>
            <li>Support local awareness campaigns</li>
            <li>Identify at-risk zones like factories, hotels, garages</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

